doc.after: The Philippines' international relations are based on trade with other nations and the well-being of the 11Â million overseas Filipinos living outside the country.[149] As a founding and active member of the United Nations, the Philippines has been elected several times into the Security Council. Carlos P. Romulo was a former President of the United Nations General Assembly. The country is an active participant in the Human Rights Council as well as in peacekeeping missions, particularly in East Timor.[150][151][152]
